Issue Description

A user reported that their network printer appeared Offline and was unable to print documents. The issue began following scheduled weekend maintenance. Restarting the workstation did not restore printer connectivity.

Symptoms
Printer displayed Offline in Windows.
Print jobs remained in the print queue.
Unable to print documents.
Workstation restarted with no improvement.
Issue began after scheduled weekend maintenance.
Troubleshooting Performed
Connected to the user's workstation using the Remote Support tool.
Verified the printer status in Devices and Printers.
Confirmed the printer was showing as Offline.
Removed the existing printer configuration from the workstation.
Re-added the printer using its IP address.
Installed the appropriate printer configuration.
Printed a test page.
Confirmed the printer status changed to Online and printing functionality was restored.
Resolution

Removed the offline printer configuration and reinstalled the printer using its network IP address. Verified successful communication with the printer by printing a test page.

Status: Resolved

Root Cause

Following scheduled maintenance, the existing printer connection was no longer communicating correctly with the network printer. Recreating the printer connection using the printer's IP address established a new, functional network connection.

Preventive Recommendations
Use TCP/IP printer ports for network printers where appropriate to improve connection reliability.
Verify printer connectivity after scheduled maintenance or infrastructure changes.
Keep printer drivers updated using approved vendor releases.
Maintain an inventory of printer IP addresses and configurations for quicker incident resolution.
Technical Summary

The workstation retained an offline printer configuration after the weekend maintenance. The existing printer connection was removed and recreated using the printer's IP address, establishing a new TCP/IP printer port. After reinstalling the printer, communication with the print device was successfully restored, and a test print confirmed normal operation.

Real-World Equivalent
Simulator Step	Real IT Environment
Remote Support	Microsoft Quick Assist, BeyondTrust, TeamViewer, ConnectWise Control
