Industry Context

This is a common Tier 1 Service Desk incident. After maintenance, network printers may appear offline due to changes in network configuration, print server updates, or corrupted printer mappings. A standard troubleshooting approach is to verify printer connectivity, remove any stale printer configuration, and re-add the printer using its IP address or the organization's print server. Before resolving the incident, technicians should always confirm that the printer reports Online and successfully prints a test page.
